November 5 2019 Write-In Report

Notice regarding write-ins: The Write-In Report (posted above) details the names of “write-in” votes cast electronically at the polls on Election Day; it does not include the names of write-in votes that were cast by paper ballot (i.e., Mail-In, Provisional, or Emergency ballots); names written in on paper ballots are detailed separately and are available from our office upon request. Note: While the names are detailed separately, the actual “Write In” totals shown on the Summary report represent the cumulative total from all write-in sources, i.e., voting machines, mail-in ballots, and any provisional or emergency ballots cast.

June 5 2018 List of Primary Write-In Winners*

Note that write-ins for county and municipal office are required to receive a minimum number of votes in order to win the nomination of their party (the same number as signatures that would have been required on a petition for that office). If a particular race you’re interested in does not appear on the list of winners, it means the party’s minimum vote requirement was not reached and no write-ins were eligible to receive a nomination. *Names of Party County Committee write-in winners are not included on this list; a list of county committee write-in winners is available from your municipal clerk.
